    {\displaystyle i}
  -th component.
The Jacobian matrix, whose entries are functions of x, is denoted in various ways; common notations include Df, Jf, 
  
    
      
        ∇
        
          f
        
      
    
    {\displaystyle \nabla \mathbf {f} }
  , and 
  
    
      
        
          
            
              ∂
              (
              
                f
                
                  1
                
              
              ,
              .
              .
              ,
              
                f
                
                  m
                
              
              )
            
            
              ∂
              (
              
                x
                
                  1
                
              
              ,
              .
              .
              ,
              
